data.title: My life as an NPC- Part 1

images.description:
I'm a baker. I work in a very unique situation- my kitchen is very public so a lot of people know me but I do not know the people. I am part of a ton of people's daily commute since 2 major transit lines pass my work, and a lot of people walk.

I would like to offer some insight on what I do most days.
I work at 4 am. Luckily I work about 4 minutes from my house so I can sleep in a little bit. It takes me about 30 minutes to shower, dress, braid my hair and drink 2 coffees.
I drink more coffee when I get to work. I probably drink about 8 coffees a day. I also drink about 4 litres of water.

images.description:
My sister Evalynn has ended her terrible battle with colorectal cancer tonight and has passed away.

Struggling with it for almost a year now. The disease 1 in every 24 women will have, my sister fought it and has lost.
She was 29 years old and as her younger brother I'm lost. She's always been my best friend and buddy all my life and without her I'm clueless.
Rest in peace. I love you and wish I could have helped.

My sister every year donated to St. Jude, she was a teacher and loved kids more than herself. 
Donate if you can to St. Jude's hospital.

Thanks for letting me post here, I know how annoying it may seem to see sad posts. I just feel like the world is a smaller place without her here. Her love and passion for others.

data.title: The fantastically disturbing art of Trevor Henderson.

images.description:
#1) The RV refusing to start quickly became the least of their worries. The thing that had been circling them had started getting bold. And by his watch, it was noon, and still pitch-black outside. The headlights flickered as it circled past the windshield once again.

_____
He combines real photos with digital painting to create creepy, eerie artworks. Each one comes with a short little caption, which can take a painting from uncanny to downright disturbing. Some pieces are subtle, and it takes a moment to find the hidden monster(s), whilst some are far more in your face. If you like SCPs, you're sure to like this. Check out his blog here: http://slimyswampghost.tumblr.com
#2) the house wakes up
#3) He found himself someplace new, and this time there was something else here in these tunnels with him. Fleeting glimpses told him he most likely didn’t want to introduce himself.

Today last year I was being cheated on for the second time. It was the end of seven years, and I was mocked and cast aside because I didn't support having his new relationship rubbed in my face. 
You're on Imgur, it's too much to hope for that one day karma will find you. You know what you did wrong, and I agree with everyone when they say I deserved better than you.

**Edit. Thank you everyone for your support, I've read every comment and appreciate them all. Oli, I could badmouth you,. But your not worth it**

Bladesmithing - Getting Started
data.description: Showing my first year of becoming a bladesmith

images.description:
After watching several seasons of Forged In Fire, I thought bladesmithing looked like a fun hobby, though wasn't sure how to get started.  One item I knew I needed was an anvil, but didn't want to spend the $500 for an entry level forging anvil.  Especially on a new hobby that I may find I don't actually like.

Lucky for me, I came up on my 5 year work anniversary at OST, and was offered a very nice watch as a present.  I asked, and was granted, to select something of equal or lesser value for my gift.  My new 77lbs Kanca anvil arrive via UPS about a week later!

https://www.centaurforge.com/Kanca-77-lbs-Drop-Forged-Double-Horn-Anvil-35-KG/productinfo/DFA77DH/
Freshly unpacked anvil.  Aside from a few other common tools, this is how it started.
Living in the city, I don't have many options for workspaces.  I resigned myself to parking in the driveway, and began building a workbench.

data.title: Doorways I've encountered on my travels

images.description:
I'm passionate about exploring the world with my camera, and have been lucky enough to visit some special places over the last 10 years, I thought I'd like to share some of that.

Above, A tomb in the Shah-i-Zinda Necopolis in Samarkand, Uzbekistan, central Asian architecture is so damn colourful, it was one of my favourite trips places to explore.
Another colourful example central Asian decoration. A small corner of the massive Registan complex in Samarkand, Uzbekistan. these areas are now used as art shops.

Church of the Holy Sepulchre in Jerusalem, I was wandering the streets taking pictures late at night and stumbled upon midnight mass, apart from a small group of people I had the whole church to myself.
